	span Grid System

p
	| Concise uses the <a href="https://github.com/jameskolce/atgrid.css" target="_blank">atGrid</a>
	| grid system built by Concise contributor <a href="http://jameskolce.com/" target="_blank">James Kolce</a>.
	| This system relies primarily on HTML attributes for building out rows and columns.
	| However, mixins are also included for writing semantic markup

p.note
	| Please refer to our documentation on <a href="/documentation">mixins</a>
	| to see arguments and outputs for each mixin.

p
	| By default, the grid system has a container width of <code>1200px</code>,
	| 12 columns, and <code>30px</code> gutters.

p.note
	| You can find all of the configuration for the Concise grid inside
	| of <code>/custom/_globals.scss</code>.

h2 Containers

p
	| You can wrap content in the <code>container</code> attribute to set a max
	| width of <b>1200px</b> and center content. Alternatively, you can use
	| the <code>container()</code> mixin to create semantic containers.

